%% 3.1.7 Driver Management — sequence (layered)
%% Actor > UI > Controller > Service > Repository > Database

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Actor as Admin or Staff
    participant UI as UI (/drivers)
    participant UC as Controller (UserController)
    participant US as Service (UserService)
    participant Repo as Repository (IRepository User)
    participant DB as Database (SQL Server)

    Actor->>UI: Click Create Driver
    UI->>UI: Show form — Name, Email, Password, License fields, Datepicker

    opt Avatar image (optional FE flow)
        UI->>UI: Upload image → get URL (e.g. Cloudinary) if integrated
    end

    Actor->>UI: Fill fields, pick License Expiry via calendar (BR07: disable past)

    UI->>UC: POST /api/User/CreateDriver (DriverCreateDto)
    UC->>US: CreateDriverAsync(dto)

    alt BR07 — expiry not after today
        US->>US: Validate DriverLicenseExpiryDate greater than UtcNow date
        US-->>UC: throw
        UC-->>UI: 400 Bad Request
        UI-->>Actor: Error message
    else Valid driver
        US->>Repo: Add User role driver + license fields + hash password
        Repo->>DB: INSERT
        DB-->>Repo: OK
        Repo-->>US: saved
        US-->>UC: DriverDto
        UC-->>UI: 200 Success
        UI-->>Actor: Celebratory Toast
    end
